data.chText: 细菌一进入血液里，就附着在红细胞表面上。
data.enText: Once in the bloodstream, the bacteria adhere to the surface of the red cells.

data.chText: 坚持，遵守，遵循（法律、规章、指示、信念等）
data.enText: to behave according to a particular law, rule, set of instructions, etc.; to follow a particular set of beliefs or a fixed way of doing sth

data.chText: 十个月来他严格坚持无脂肪少盐饮食。
data.enText: For ten months he adhered to a strict no-fat low-salt diet.

data.chText: 她依循她30多年前所学的教学法教学。
data.enText: She adheres to teaching methods she learned over 30 years ago.

simple_means.memory_skill: ad 做…或加强 + her 粘 + e → 坚持；粘附

ex.enText: This glue doesn't stick very well.

ex.chText: 他给每个信封都贴了一张邮票。
ex.enText: He stuck a stamp on every envelope.
Her shirt was sticking to her back.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，常指用胶水、胶带等黏性物质粘贴某物，有时也指衣物等因出汗而粘在身上。

ex.chText: 新涂的油漆在墙上粘不住，因此我得把它全部刮掉。
ex.enText: The new paint doesn't adhere to the walls so I'll have to strip it all off.

synonyms.bx: 指紧紧粘在某物上，常后接介词 to，与 stick 相比粘贴得更牢固。

ex.enText: Please glue stick the stamp onto the envelope.

ex.chText: 你能把破碎的花瓶黏合起来吗?
ex.enText: Can you glue the broken vase together?

synonyms.bx: 指用胶水把东西黏合在一起，与 stick基本同义，常可换用。

data.chText: 坚持，遵守，遵循（法律、规章、指示、信念等）
data.enText: to behave according to a particular law, rule, set of instructions, etc.; to follow a particular set of beliefs or a fixed way of doing sth

data.chText: 十个月来他严格坚持无脂肪少盐饮食。
data.enText: For ten months he adhered to a strict no-fat low-salt diet.

data.chText: 她依循她30多年前所学的教学法教学。
data.enText: She adheres to teaching methods she learned over 30 years ago.

tr: follow through or carry out a plan without deviation
come or be in close contact with
stick or hold together and resist separation
example: The dress clings to her body
The label stuck to the box
Will this wallpaper adhere to the wall?
She stood by her husband in times of trouble
The friends stuck together through the war

tr: be a devoted follower or supporter
example: The residents of this village adhered to Catholicism

tr: be compatible or in accordance with
example: You must adhere to the rules

value.def: If you adhere to a rule or agreement, you act in the way that it says you should.

example.ex: All members of the association adhere to a strict code of practice...
example.tran: 协会的所有成员都遵守一套严格的行为规范。

example.ex: She adhered to the strict Islamic dress code.
example.tran: 她恪守伊斯兰教严格的着装规定。

value.def: If you adhere to an opinion or belief, you support or hold it.

example.ex: He urged them to adhere to the values of Islam which defend the dignity of man.
example.tran: 他鼓励他们坚守伊斯兰教维护人类尊严的价值观。

value.tran: 支持，拥护，持有（观点或信仰）

value.def: If something adheres to something else, it sticks firmly to it.

example.ex: Small particles adhere to the seed...
example.tran: 小颗粒牢牢附着在种子上。

example.ex: This sticky compound adheres well on this surface.
example.tran: 这种黏性的化合物能牢牢地粘在这个表面上。
